📘 Day 2 – CompTIA A+ Revision Sheet
1. What is BIOS?

👉
“BIOS (Basic Input/Output System) is firmware stored on the motherboard that initializes hardware and starts the boot process when the computer is powered on.”

2. What is POST?

👉
“POST (Power-On Self-Test) is a process performed by BIOS to check if hardware components like RAM, CPU, and keyboard are working properly.”

3. What is Operating System?

👉
“Operating System is system software that manages hardware resources and provides an interface between user and computer, like Windows, Linux.”

4. What is Booting?

👉
“Booting is the process of starting a computer and loading the operating system into memory.”

5. Types of Booting?

👉
“Cold boot is starting the computer from OFF state, and warm boot is restarting the system.”

6. What is SSD vs NVMe?

👉
“Both are SSDs, but NVMe is faster because it uses PCIe interface, while SATA SSD uses slower SATA interface.”

7. What is Cache Memory?

👉
“Cache memory is small, high-speed memory inside CPU that stores frequently used data to improve performance.”

8. What is GPU?

👉
“GPU (Graphics Processing Unit) is responsible for rendering images, videos, and graphics.”

9. Difference between Integrated and Dedicated GPU?

👉
“Integrated GPU is built into CPU and shares system memory, while dedicated GPU has its own memory and provides better performance.”

10. What is IP Address?

👉
“IP address is a unique identifier assigned to a device on a network.”

11. What is DHCP?

👉
“DHCP automatically assigns IP addresses to devices in a network.”

12. What is DNS?

👉
“DNS converts domain names into IP addresses so computers can locate websites.”

13. What is Firewall?

👉
“Firewall is a security system that monitors and controls incoming and outgoing network traffic.”

14. What is Antivirus?

👉
“Antivirus is software that detects and removes malicious programs from a computer.”

15. Internet not working — what will you check?

👉
“I will check network cable or Wi-Fi connection, IP address, restart router, and verify network settings.”

16. What is Blue Screen Error?

👉
“Blue Screen Error occurs when the system crashes due to hardware or driver issues.”

17. What is Driver?

👉
“Driver is software that allows the operating system to communicate with hardware devices.”

18. Printer not working — what will you do?

👉
“I will check power, cable connection, printer status, drivers, and restart the printer and system.”

19. What is Virtual Memory?

👉
“Virtual memory is a portion of hard disk used as RAM when actual RAM is full.”

20. What is Formatting?

👉
“Formatting prepares a storage device for use by creating a file system.”
